   January 30, 2002         DOL > Frequently Asked Questions

   Frequently Asked Questions


                                                      Additional Resources



   Use our Search / A-Z Index to browse an alphabetical listing of topics
   on this site and locate documents via a keyword search.

   Find It! Interfaces provide links to resources on our Web site sorted
   by Topic, by Organization, by Form, by Audience, by Location and by Top
   20 Requested Items.

   The elaws Advisors are interactive tools that provide information about
   federal employment laws. Each Advisor simulates an interaction between
   you and an employment law expert. It asks questions and provides
   answers based on your responses.

   We have compiled frequently asked questions on various topics within
   the U.S. Department of Labor. Search for the topic of your question
   from the list below.

   Contracting  Contains information about the Federal Contractor
   Program, affirmative action, and equal pay.

   Disability  Provides information on the Job Accommodation Network
   (JAN), personal assistance services in the workplace, pre-employment
   inquiries, tax incentives for business, special minimum wage rates, and
   the Work Opportunity Tax Credit Program.

   Employment Assistance  Contains information for dislocated workers and
   answers questions about the Occupational Information Network (O*NET).

   Employment Standards  Provides information about the Family and
   Medical Leave Act, wage and hour requirements, child labor,
   contracting, workers' compensation, and how workplace laws apply to
   welfare recipients.

   Mining  Provides information about the Federal Black Lung Program.

   Office of Administrative Law Judges  Provides an overview of the
   office and its role, function, and responsibilities.

   Pension & Health Plans & Benefits  Information on the employee
   benefits laws administered and enforced by the Department of Labor,
   including the Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA),
   Consolidated Omnibus Budget Reconciliation Act (COBRA), and Health
   Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA).

   Safety & Health  Contains a broad range of safety and health
   information affecting employees and employers.

   Statistics  Provides information on employment and unemployment data;
   prices and living conditions; compensation and working conditions,
   productivity and technology; and employment projections.

   Veterans  Provides information on military transferring to civilian
   careers.

   Wage & Hour  Information about minimum wage, overtime, recordkeeping,
   vacation pay, and other wage and hour questions.

   Women in the Workplace  Provides information on the many issues that
   pertain to women in the workplace.

   Youth & Labor  Contains information about child labor standards,
   getting a job, and the Youth Opportunity Movement.
